&lt;Westmin Resources Ltd> said itplans to increase capacity at its Myra Falls, British Columbia,base and precious metal mine and mill complex by 33 pct to4,400 tons of ore a day, subject to regulatory approvals.    The company said the expansion will cost about 24 mln dlrsand could be in operation by 1988.    Economies of scale from the expansion should pay back netexpansion cost in less than one year, Westmin said.    The Myra Falls complex processed 3,257 tons of ore a dayduring 1986. Reuter&#3;